the national compiler infrastructure project the national compiler infrastructure project the national compiler infrastructure project aims to develop a common compiler platform to support the collaboration of compiler researchers and to facilitate the transfer of technology to industry co funded by darpa and nsf the national compiler infrastructure project has two components suif the suif component is a collaboration between researchers in four universities harvard university massachusetts institute of technology rice university stanford university uc santa barbara and one industrial partner portland group inc zephyr the zephyr component is a collaboration between princeton university and university of virginia overall structure of the proposed national compiler infrastructure please use our mailing lists and archives to give us feedback hear what others have to say and find out about the latest news last updated on january 12 1998
